be able to work in FX.

firefox jetpack code to take advantage of warner's new jetpack crypto module
move account creation and sign in into background module

changes to support shallow freeze of modules in Jetpack
have the FX tld modulke return the full domain in the case of any error
Tld and SiteConfig modules for FX
basic messaging shim for Firefox to be compatible with our messaging interface

restructure Firefox code so that it doesn't live in a separate dir

Jetpack allows us to use any directory in our add-on in place of lib/main.js, so I've moved all of that code into background/firefox-main.js.

However, Jetpack still requires content scripts/assets to be in /data. So I scrapped the original /Firefox directory, and moved the original /Firefox/data dir to a top level /data directory, and updated the symlinks accordingly.
detecting forms in content scripts and able to message to firefox background
fixed an exception raised when the extension attempted to link when there is no user logged in
have bundler delete server/node_modules, bump up version number
finally something people can look at
maintain logged in sessions across browser sessions
unlock sign in form if user has a log in error
show user email (and sign out link) in gombot button popup
only show the divider in gombot button popup if we're signed into the extension
do user.fetch() before showing linking notification
